<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>in the ketchup • on the sauce</xh5><p> <i>in the ketchup</i>—(U.S. sl.) said of a business, etc. that fails to show a profit: Ridgway has wound up <u>in the ketchup</u> trying to operate a gym.</p><p> <i>on the sauce</i>—(sl.) drinking heavily: You’re not in debt, <u>on the sauce</u>, going gay ... I can’t blackmail you.</p> </entry>
